01:32.440 --> 01:37.680
you may try and make coding choices that make people say wow he or she is so smart.

01:37.690 --> 01:42.110
Or I have no idea what they just quoted but it looks so cool.

01:42.130 --> 01:43.540
This is not good.

01:43.570 --> 01:50.560
Too often I see developers choose complex options or coding styles in order to seem smart and capable

01:51.340 --> 01:57.380
or just use a cool new function or trick that they recently learned.

01:57.390 --> 02:06.430
Now the secret that the best developers I know use is that they always choose simplicity over complexity.

02:07.220 --> 02:12.020
Writing code isn't a measure of how smart you are and how many things you know.

02:12.020 --> 02:16.450
Writing code is about creating something that is of good quality.

02:16.450 --> 02:18.120
What do I mean by that.

02:18.260 --> 02:21.320
Good code is self documenting.

02:21.530 --> 02:27.990
It is easy for someone new to come in look at your code and understand what it does.

02:28.160 --> 02:32.920
Right away good code also minimizes bugs.

02:32.930 --> 02:38.630
It allows people to not add bugs on top of it because it's clear and concise.

02:38.630 --> 02:45.710
It's easy to read simplicity in code is making your code readable as if you just reading an English

